# MarkRight Tooling Roadmap

## Must-Have for Launch

- [x] npm package (WASM wrapper)
  Publish the Rust parser as an npm package via wasm-pack.
  Everything downstream in the JS ecosystem depends on this.

- [x] HTML renderer
  AST to HTML conversion.
  Needed for playground, SSG plugins, preview panes, and web rendering.

- [x] TextMate grammar
  `.tmLanguage.json` for MarkRight syntax.
  Unlocks VS Code, Sublime, GitHub code view, Shiki, and Linguist registration.
  Single highest-leverage syntax artifact.

- [x] VS Code extension
  Syntax highlighting via TextMate grammar + live preview via WASM.
  VS Code has ~74% dev market share.

- [x] Tree-sitter grammar
  `grammar.js` + `highlights.scm` queries.
  Unlocks Neovim, Zed, Helix, Emacs, and GitHub code view.

- [x] Online playground
  Browser-based editor with live rendered output.
  WASM-powered, no install required.
  Typst credits their playground as the best acquisition funnel.

## High Priority

- [x] LSP implementation
  Rust-based using `tower-lsp`.
  Document symbols, formatting, lint diagnostics, and go-to-definition for footnotes.

- [x] Formatter
  Canonical source formatting (AST to source serialization).
  MarkRight has "one right way" -- the formatter enforces it.

- [x] Pandoc reader/writer
  Lua scripts converting MarkRight to/from Pandoc AST.
  Gives conversion to every format for free: PDF, DOCX, EPUB, LaTeX, Markdown, RST.

- [ ] GitHub Linguist registration
  PR to `github-linguist/linguist`.
  Requires the TextMate grammar + public repos using `.right`.

- [x] Neovim support
  `ftdetect`, Tree-sitter queries, LSP config.
  Nearly free once Tree-sitter grammar and LSP exist.

- [x] Zed extension
  Tree-sitter grammar + LSP config.
  Nearly free once those two exist.

- [x] SSG plugins
  Vite plugin transforms `.right` files to HTML modules with front matter.
  Works with Astro, SvelteKit, Nuxt, and any Vite-based SSG.

- [x] JSON Schema for AST
  Enables AI agents to generate valid MarkRight via structured output.
  Novel -- no other markup language does this yet.

## Nice-to-Have

- [x] MCP server
  AI agents can parse `.right` files, query structure, validate syntax.
  No markup language has one yet -- differentiator.

- [x] JetBrains plugin
  TextMate bundle for syntax highlighting.
  Install via Settings > Editor > TextMate Bundles, point to editors/jetbrains.

- [x] Standalone linter
  CI-friendly: heading level skips, unused/undefined/duplicate footnotes,
  duplicate heading IDs. Integrated into `markright --lint`, MCP, WASM, and LSP diagnostics.

- [-] highlight.js / Prism grammars
  Superseded by Shiki, which uses our TextMate grammar directly.

- [x] Native PDF export
  Covered by Pandoc: `pandoc -f pandoc/reader.lua input.right -o output.pdf`

- [-] Obsidian plugin
  Deferred until broader adoption. Obsidian is deeply tied to `.md`.

- [x] Markdown-to-MarkRight converter
  Migration tool. Also generates training data for LLMs to learn MarkRight syntax.
  Done via Pandoc writer: `pandoc -f markdown -t pandoc/markright.lua input.md`
